Whereas the Joshua Omvig Suicide Prevention Act (Public Law 110–110; 121 Stat. 1031) was enacted in
			 2007 to establish a comprehensive program for suicide prevention among
			 veterans;

Whereas the Veterans Crisis Line, which was established under the Joshua Omvig Suicide Prevention
			 Act, has received more than 890,000 telephone calls and facilitated more
			 than 30,000 life-saving rescues;
